'''Dorset House''' was a large house in [[Headington]], [[Oxford]], [[England]].<ref name="headington">{{cite web| url=http://www.headington.org.uk/history/buildings/dorsethouse.htm | title=Dorset House, 58 London Road | work=Headington history: Non-listed buildings | publisher=www.headington.org.uk | location=UK | accessdate=29 January 2018 }}</ref>
This [[villa]], known in its later years as Dorset House, was built in 1878 on the south side of [[London Road, Oxford]]. It had various names during its lifetime:<ref name="headington" />
* 1878–1899: '''Ellerslie''' * 1899–1920: '''Hillstow''' * 1920–1961: '''Hillstow Annexe''', [[Headington School]] * 1961–2004: '''Dorset House''', School of [[Occupational Therapy]]
[[Catherine Caughey]] (1923–2008), who worked on codebreaking at [[Bletchley Park]] during [[World War II]], subsequently trained as an [[occupational therapist]] at Dorset House.<ref name="copeland17">{{cite book| authorlink1=Jack Copeland | last1=Copeland | first1=Jack | authorlink2=Jonathan Bowen | last2=Bowen | first2=Jonathan | last3=Sprevak | first3=Mark | authorlink4=Robin Wilson (mathematician) | last4=Wilson | first4=Robin | author5=et al. | title=[[The Turing Guide]] | publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] | year=2017 | isbn=978-0198747833 | pages=476 | chapter=Notes on Contributors }}</ref>
The house was acquired by [[Quintain Estates and Development|Quintain]] property developers in 2006 and demolished in 2009.<ref name="headington" /> Quintain sold the site to [[Berkeley Homes]] in September 2010 for £5m. The site was developed as [[student housing]] for [[Oxford Brookes University]] students during 2011–12.<ref>{{cite news| date=2 April 2011 | title=Student flats plan gets the go-ahead | first=Chris | last=Buratta | url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/8949255.Student_flats_plan_gets_the_go_ahead/ | newspaper=[[Oxford Mail]] | location=UK }}</ref> and is managed by [[Unite Students|Unite]], still under the name of Dorset House.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.brookes.ac.uk/studying-at-brookes/accommodation/returning-students/dorset-house/ | title=Dorset House | publisher=[[Oxford Brookes University]] | location=UK | accessdate=29 January 2018 }}</ref>
