'''Timothy S. Jost''' is a professor at the [[Washington and Lee University School of Law]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://law.wlu.edu/faculty/profiledetail.asp?id=24|title=Faculty : W&L Law School|publisher=Law.wlu.edu|accessdate=13 November 2014}}</ref> He is the co-author of ''Health Law'', a widely used textbook. His analysis and arguments regarding the [[Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act]] (ACA, Obamacare) have been widely quoted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaelcannon/2014/07/14/the-halbig-cases-timothy-jost-responds-guest-post/|title=The Halbig Cases: Timothy Jost Responds (Guest Post)|author=Michael F. Cannon|date=14 July 2014|work=Forbes|accessdate=13 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/courts-wont-void-the-affordable-care-act-over-semantics/2014/07/09/5910c9d0-060b-11e4-a0dd-f2b22a257353_story.html|title=Courts won’t void the Affordable Care Act over semantics|work=Washington Post|accessdate=13 November 2014}}</ref>

